text:
Hi Tessa, thanks for the link it had some very valuable advice. How are you holding up during all this? Hopefully you've been able to start working from home, either way stay safe.
On a lighter note, here is a quick update of the shots I've been working on. A developed Sh05 - <https://syncsketch.com/sketch/d60b026a1348/> thank you for the crit, it was a huge help :slightly_smiling_face:, I think this shot is almost ready to render, but if there is anything that sticks out please don't hesitate to point it out. Here is Sh01 <https://syncsketch.com/sketch/78370869e13e/>, I've gotten this shot blocked and have done a first pass on it, again if there is anything that sticks out as non-dog-like please let me know, I'll have more to show soon, and I'll try my best to keep you updated :slightly_smiling_face:

Hey Josh. Things are good on this end. I started working from home since this Wednesday, which I'm very happy about. I had a quick look at your shots. Sh05 is definitely looking better, and Sh01 has a lot of good stuff going on. I do have some notes one both, so I'll see if I can get those to you soon. :slightly_smiling_face: Awesome to see an update!
